From 70b64ba67c35527f916ea279e7c91253263ac115 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 14:56:17 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 40/41] inline-3d(#625): delay-load openxr_loader.dll so the
 sandboxed renderer survives
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A patched non-component build never showed a browser window (displayxr-browser#15),
and nothing of ours had to run: with zero flags set, chrome.dll's import table
alone did it.

In a component build the OpenXR loader import lands in the weave_client DLL,
which only the browser and GPU processes load. In a non-component build every
component collapses into chrome.dll, so chrome.dll itself imports
openxr_loader.dll — and every process must resolve it at load time. The renderer
is sandboxed (low integrity, restricted token) and cannot load a DLL outside its
policy, so it died before running any Blink code. Measured against vanilla on the
same box: identical browser/gpu/utility/crashpad counts, 3 renderers vs our 0;
--no-sandbox brought 4 renderers back, isolating the sandbox from a crash. Zero
renderers is what produced the symptom — the toolbar WebUI JS never ran, so
BrowserView::Show()'s deferred-show gate never released.

The fix delay-loads the loader so it resolves on the first xr* call. Renderers
never make one; the browser (unsandboxed) and GPU (weave inits pre-sandbox in
gpu_main.cc) processes that do are safe.

Placement matters: a /DELAYLOAD ldflag in third_party/displayxr's link config does
NOT reach chrome.dll — `libs` propagate transitively to the final link
automatically, but a config's `ldflags` only propagate through an unbroken
public_configs chain, which breaks before chrome.dll. So the entry lives in
//build/config/win:delayloads_except_dbghelp, alongside d3d11/dxgi/dcomp, which
chrome_dll pulls in directly.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 build/config/win/BUILD.gn      | 10 ++++++++++
 third_party/displayxr/BUILD.gn | 10 ++++++++++
 2 files changed, 20 insertions(+)

diff --git a/build/config/win/BUILD.gn b/build/config/win/BUILD.gn
index 101c2339697ca..f00fed5c7e01a 100644
--- a/build/config/win/BUILD.gn
+++ b/build/config/win/BUILD.gn
@@ -433,6 +433,16 @@ config("delayloads_except_dbghelp") {
     "/DELAYLOAD:netapi32.dll",
     "/DELAYLOAD:ncrypt.dll",
     "/DELAYLOAD:ole32.dll",
+
+    # DisplayXR inline-3D (#625, displayxr-browser#15): the vendored OpenXR
+    # loader. Only the browser and GPU processes ever call an xr* function; in a
+    # non-component build chrome.dll's static import of it would otherwise force
+    # the sandboxed renderer to resolve the DLL at load time, which it cannot do
+    # (low integrity, restricted token) — the renderer dies before running any
+    # Blink code and the browser window never shows. Delay-loading resolves it on
+    # first use instead, exactly like the d3d11/dxgi/dcomp entries above.
+    "/DELAYLOAD:openxr_loader.dll",
+
     "/DELAYLOAD:oleacc.dll",
     "/DELAYLOAD:oleaut32.dll",
     "/DELAYLOAD:pdh.dll",
diff --git a/third_party/displayxr/BUILD.gn b/third_party/displayxr/BUILD.gn
index 3ecafc90fb7c5..0b91c0057a95e 100644
--- a/third_party/displayxr/BUILD.gn
+++ b/third_party/displayxr/BUILD.gn
@@ -16,6 +16,16 @@ config("openxr_headers") {
 
 # Link the prebuilt OpenXR loader import lib (CRT-neutral). lib_dirs is resolved
 # relative to this BUILD.gn directory.
+#
+# NOTE (displayxr-browser#15): openxr_loader.dll MUST be delay-loaded in a
+# non-component build, or chrome.dll's static import of it kills the sandboxed
+# renderer at load time (it can't load a DLL outside its policy) — zero
+# renderers, and the browser window never shows. A /DELAYLOAD ldflag here does
+# NOT work: `libs` propagate transitively to chrome.dll's link automatically, but
+# a config's `ldflags` only propagate through an unbroken public_configs chain,
+# which breaks before chrome.dll. So the delay-load lives where it is guaranteed
+# to reach the final link — //build/config/win:delayloads_except_dbghelp,
+# alongside d3d11/dxgi/dcomp — which chrome_dll pulls in directly.
 config("openxr_loader_link") {
   libs = [ "openxr_loader.lib" ]
   lib_dirs = [ "lib" ]
-- 
